    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_GrantExecuteToFunction",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to grant permissions to Active Directory users on SQL Server functions. Specifically, it grants "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "EXECUTE",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " permissions on functions that do not start with 'uftn_' and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SELECT",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " permissions on those that do. The procedure uses a cursor to iterate over all functions in the database, checking their names and applying the appropriate permissions to the specified domain user."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this stored procedure is considered medium due to the following factors:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It involves dynamic SQL execution."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It uses a cursor to iterate over database objects."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It includes conditional logic to determine the type of permission to grant based on function names."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@ActiveDirectoryDomainName NVARCHAR(256)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter specifies the domain name of the Active Directory user to whom permissions will be granted."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@DomainUserName NVARCHAR(256)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter specifies the username of the Active Directory user within the domain."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
